The water uptake is a measure of how the membrane mass changes when exposed to water [116]. It is calculated as a per cent difference between wet and dry membrane masses. The “dry” membrane state is defined the same as above for IEC.8WU=mw-mdmd∗100%.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
