The membrane water content is a measure of the number of water molecules per mobile anion and is calculated by dividing the water uptake by the molecular weight of water and IEC [117]. Note that the WU is multiplied by 10 to account for the WU being reported in per cent and the IEC being reported in mmol/g.9γ=10∗WUMWH2O∗IEC.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
